      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-12-07T21:25:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ah, the problem seems to be sizeof() on a non-instance. i.e.\n\nstruct X {\n  int a[1];\n};\n\nint main() {\n  sizeof(X);  // OK\n  sizeof(X::a);  //  error C2070: \u0027unknown\u0027: illegal sizeof operand\n  X x;\n  sizeof(x.a);  // OK\n}\n\nSo I guess using `kSecDescBlob.` instead of `SecurityDescriptorBlob::` is tidier.",
      "parentUuid": "ed7c572f_2f6da5aa",
      "revId": "81772a3028ce44a4ef3f1985c61656e0d76cd0bd",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
